    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/sheikhashadul/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=608106698237805466&sectionId=608112356739777434)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"ggxCXeVESn3_text","label":"ggxCXeVESn3_text","default":"<p>Gary Whitfield will never forget the morning his wife called him into the bathroom, face white as a sheet, hands shaking.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggpGP2uv-b6_text","label":"ggpGP2uv-b6_text","default":"<p>It was a Wednesday in March. Ten days into what Gary had assumed was just another failed experiment in a two-year string of them.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggWdyfFN3DU_text","label":"ggWdyfFN3DU_text","default":"<p>But what Sarah Whitfield showed him that morning wasn't failure.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggj7Vm-UNaG_text","label":"ggj7Vm-UNaG_text","default":"<p>There, in the toilet, were rope-like masses. Mucus-covered. Dense. Unmistakable.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg_6svzOBi7_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"gg_6svzOBi7_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0993/4700/5732/files/istockphoto-1147544807-612x612_copy.jpg"},{"type":"html","id":"ggihbwY3P5__text","label":"ggihbwY3P5__text","default":"<p>Biofilm. The invisible fortress that had been protecting parasites inside Sarah's intestinal wall for years — hiding them from her immune system, from lab tests, from every doctor, supplement, and elimination diet she'd tried.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggiO5AWU0es_text","label":"ggiO5AWU0es_text","default":"<p>Finally breaking apart. Finally releasing. Finally coming out.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggu2H7mQNou_text","label":"ggu2H7mQNou_text","default":"<p><i>\"We just held each other and cried. Two years of doctors saying it's just IBS. Two years of eliminating food after food. And the answer had been parasites hiding behind biofilm the entire time.\"</i> — Gary Whitfield, 46, Austin, TX</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggvL3mfWHHm_text","label":"ggvL3mfWHHm_text","default":"<p>What Gary discovered — and what ultimately ended his wife's nightmare — wasn't a new drug, a new diet, or a new supplement.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggVIobg_dhe_text","label":"ggVIobg_dhe_text","default":"<p>It was something far older. A delivery method our grandparents used routinely. One that bypasses the stomach entirely and reaches the intestinal wall directly — where parasites actually live.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggn1gbAGt5U_text","label":"ggn1gbAGt5U_text","default":"<p>But first, let me show you exactly how bad it got.</p>"}],
    "blocks": [{"type": "@app"}],
    "locales": {}
  }
